      • getSequences

        public static <T> java.util.List<java.util.List<T>> getSequences(java.util.List<T> items,
                                                                 int length)
                                                          throws JMEInterruptedException
        Get all sequences with a specific length
        Sample:
        * length:2,[1,2] -> [[1,1],[1,2],[2,1],[2,2]]
        * length:3,[1] -> [[1,1,1]]
        * length:1,[1,2] -> [[1],[2]]
        The number of sequences is equal to variations with repetition of m elements taken by n (m^n)
        Parameters:
        items - a list with the items in the sequence with no duplicates
        length - size of the sequences
        Returns:
        a list with all sequences (as lists) of size 'length'
        Throws:
        JMEInterruptedException - si el hilo se interrumpe
